abstract: The Pentagon said on Tuesday 50 U.S. service members were now diagnosed with traumatic brain injury after missile strikes by Iran on a base in Iraq earlier this month, 16 more than the military had previously announced.
snippet: The Pentagon said on Tuesday 50 U.S. service members were now diagnosed with traumatic brain injury after missile strikes by Iran on a base in Iraq earlier this month, 16 more than the military had previously announced.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon said on Tuesday 50 U.S. service members were now diagnosed with traumatic brain injury after missile strikes by Iran on a base in Iraq earlier this month, 16 more than the military had previously announced.
headline_main: U.S. Says 50 Troops Now Diagnosed With Traumatic Brain Injury After Iran Strike
headline_print_headline: U.S. Says 50 Troops Now Diagnosed With Traumatic Brain Injury After Iran Strike

abstract: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's spokesperson said the U.S. Middle East plan could be a positive step after a phone call on Tuesday between Johnson and President Donald Trump.
snippet: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's spokesperson said the U.S. Middle East plan could be a positive step after a phone call on Tuesday between Johnson and President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's spokesperson said the U.S. Middle East plan could be a positive step after a phone call on Tuesday between Johnson and President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Britain Says U.S. Middle East Peace Plan Could Be Positive Step
headline_print_headline: Britain Says U.S. Middle East Peace Plan Could Be Positive Step

abstract: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday that a U.S. peace plan envisages the proposed Palestinian capital be located in Abu Dis, a neighbourhood on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
snippet: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday that a U.S. peace plan envisages the proposed Palestinian capital be located in Abu Dis, a neighbourhood on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday that a U.S. peace plan envisages the proposed Palestinian capital be located in Abu Dis, a neighbourhood on the outskirts of Jerusalem.
headline_main: Netanyahu Says Proposed Palestinian Capital Will Be in Abu Dis
headline_print_headline: Netanyahu Says Proposed Palestinian Capital Will Be in Abu Dis

abstract: Palestinian condemnation of the U.S. Middle East peace plan came swiftly on Tuesday night, with thousands protesting in Gaza and the militant Islamist group Hamas saying it would confront President Donald Trump's "aggressive" proposals.
snippet: Palestinian condemnation of the U.S. Middle East peace plan came swiftly on Tuesday night, with thousands protesting in Gaza and the militant Islamist group Hamas saying it would confront President Donald Trump's "aggressive" proposals.
lead_paragraph: GAZA — Palestinian condemnation of the U.S. Middle East peace plan came swiftly on Tuesday night, with thousands protesting in Gaza and the militant Islamist group Hamas saying it would confront President Donald Trump's "aggressive" proposals.
headline_main: Hamas Says It Will Confront Trump's 'Aggressive' Middle East Plan
headline_print_headline: Hamas Says It Will Confront Trump's 'Aggressive' Middle East Plan

abstract: Emboldened by a supportive White House, Israel appears to be barreling toward a showdown with the international community over its half-century-old settlement enterprise in the West Bank.
snippet: Emboldened by a supportive White House, Israel appears to be barreling toward a showdown with the international community over its half-century-old settlement enterprise in the West Bank.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Emboldened by a supportive White House, Israel appears to be barreling toward a showdown with the international community over its half-century-old settlement enterprise in the West Bank.
headline_main: Israel Could Clash With International Court on Settlements
headline_print_headline: Israel Could Clash With International Court on Settlements

abstract: Prime Minister Boris Johnson told President Trump on Tuesday that countries should work together to break the dominance of a small number of companies after Britain granted Chinese firm Huawei a limited role in its 5G mobile network.
snippet: Prime Minister Boris Johnson told President Trump on Tuesday that countries should work together to break the dominance of a small number of companies after Britain granted Chinese firm Huawei a limited role in its 5G mobile network.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prime Minister Boris Johnson told President Trump on Tuesday that countries should work together to break the dominance of a small number of companies after Britain granted Chinese firm Huawei a limited role in its 5G mobile network.
headline_main: Johnson Tells Trump on Huawei That Collaboration Is Needed to Diversify Market
headline_print_headline: Johnson Tells Trump on Huawei That Collaboration Is Needed to Diversify Market

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump and Britain's Prime Minister Boris Johnson "discussed critical regional and bilateral issues, including telecommunications security" in a conversation on Tuesday, White House spokesman Judd Deere said in a statement.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump and Britain's Prime Minister Boris Johnson "discussed critical regional and bilateral issues, including telecommunications security" in a conversation on Tuesday, White House spokesman Judd Deere said in a statement.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump and Britain's Prime Minister Boris Johnson "discussed critical regional and bilateral issues, including telecommunications security" in a conversation on Tuesday, White House spokesman Judd Deere said in a statement.
headline_main: Trump, Johnson Discussed 'Telecommunications' After Huawei Decision-White House
headline_print_headline: Trump, Johnson Discussed 'Telecommunications' After Huawei Decision-White House

abstract: The U.S. government on Tuesday sued five U.S. companies and three individuals, alleging they were behind hundreds of millions of fraudulent robocalls that scammed elderly Americans and others into "massive financial losses."

abstract: President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed into law a major rewrite of the rules of trade with Canada and Mexico, celebrating the fulfillment of one of his top campaign promises while declining to share the moment with Democratic lawmakers whose support was essential to getting it over the finish line.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed into law a major rewrite of the rules of trade with Canada and Mexico, celebrating the fulfillment of one of his top campaign promises while declining to share the moment with Democratic lawmakers whose support was essential to getting it over the finish line.
headline_main: Trump Celebrates Major Rewrite of North American Trade Rules
headline_print_headline: Trump Celebrates Major Rewrite of North American Trade Rules
